org.opendaylight.controller.networkconfig.neutron

Interface INeutronLoadBalancerPoolAware


  • public interface INeutronLoadBalancerPoolAware
    This interface defines the methods a service that wishes to be aware of LoadBalancerPool Rules needs to implement

    • Method Detail

      • canCreateNeutronLoadBalancerPool

        int canCreateNeutronLoadBalancerPool(NeutronLoadBalancerPool loadBalancerPool)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified loadBalancerPool can be created
        Parameters:
        loadBalancerPool - instance of proposed new LoadBalancerPool object
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the create operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • canUpdateNeutronLoadBalancerPool

        int canUpdateNeutronLoadBalancerPool(NeutronLoadBalancerPool delta,
                                   NeutronLoadBalancerPool original)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified loadBalancerPool can be changed using the specified delta
        Parameters:
        delta - updates to the loadBalancerPool object using patch semantics
        original - instance of the LoadBalancerPool object to be updated
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the update operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.
